    "body": "I've been getting the same issue a lot as well, and had just assumed it was being worked on.  As OP noted, it seems to happen more reliably when calling a function on a Truffle contract and then clicking Reject in MetaMask to prevent the transaction from going through.  \r\n\r\n\r\nI can't always get a trace in DevTools, but was just able to capture one, and lined up hyperlinks to code (changing to the actually referenced lines in reason.js as I wasn't running the latest); the first link shows the issue: \r\n\r\n- send\t@\tinpage.js:1 (note: this is MetaMask code) \r\n- (anonymous)\t@\t[reason.js:105](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/0950040b2f51da552b910599402782d33e6abea2/packages/contract/lib/reason.js#L118)\r\n- get\t@\t[reason.js:104](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/0950040b2f51da552b910599402782d33e6abea2/packages/contract/lib/reason.js#L117)\r\n- start\t@\t[override.js:61](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/0950040b2f51da552b910599402782d33e6abea2/packages/contract/lib/override.js#L61)\r\n- Promise.catch (async)\t\t\r\n- (anonymous)\t@\t[execute.js:242](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/0950040b2f51da552b910599402782d33e6abea2/packages/contract/lib/execute.js#L242)\r\n- Promise.then (async)\t\t\r\n- (anonymous)\t@\t[execute.js:206](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/0950040b2f51da552b910599402782d33e6abea2/packages/contract/lib/execute.js#L206)\r\n\r\nPoints deeper in the stack are in application code, starting with the call to the contract's method. ",
